Privacy Policy
Protecting your privacy
At Disturbia, we're committed to protecting the privacy and security of our customers and site visitors. The purpose of this statement is to clearly explain how we use and collect personal data.
If you have any questions about how we protect your privacy,
get in touch
.
For all our services, the data controller, the company that’s responsible for your privacy, is Harper & Willow Ltd (trading as Disturbia). In certain circumstances the companies listed below will also be a data controller.
How we use your information
Using our website
We use Shopify to power our website and online store. You can read more about how Shopify uses your personal information on
Shopify’s Privacy Policy
.
Your personal information may also be controlled and processed by the following companies, some of whom may transfer your personal data outside of the EEA:
Hiltonian Media Ltd
(
privacy policy
)
Apex Ecommerce Limited (
privacy policy
)
Cloudflare (
privacy policy
)
Klaviyo (
privacy center
)
Reamaze (
privacy policy
)
Yotpo Ltd (
privacy policy
)
As you use our website and app, the following information may be collected automatically using cookies, log files, web beacons, tags or pixels: web browser software information, device information, IP address, time zone, cookie information, the content or products you view, search terms, and how you interact with the website. This information is collected to load the site accurately for you, and perform usage analytics to optimise our website. It is in our legitimate interests to collect this data to prevent malicious use of our services, monitor server performance, increase security, and diagnose problems. This information might be transferred outside of the EEA.
Website analytics
We use
Google Analytics
to analyse how visitors use our website. This stores a “cookie” on your computer containing an anonymous tracking ID to allow Google to track your activity around our website. This service is subject to
Google’s Privacy Policy
. The information associated with your cookie tracking ID is deleted 14 months after your last use of our website. Learn more about how you can
control the information sent to Google
and
opt-out of Google Analytics
.
This site uses the
Lucky Orange
analytics system to help improve usability and the customer experience. Lucky Orange may record mouse clicks, mouse movements and scrolling activity. Lucky Orange may record keystroke information that you voluntarily enter on this website. Lucky Orange does not track this activity on any site that does not use the Lucky Orange system. To view and manage data that Lucky Orange has collected about you on the Disturbia website, or to opt out of future tracking, please visit
Lucky Orange’s data privacy management tool
.
Contact Form
If you fill in and submit our contact form, the information you supply will be logged or sent to us by email and only used to respond to your enquiry. It is in your legitimate interests for this data to be processed so that we can respond to your enquiry. This information is retained for as long as necessary to deal with your enquiry.
Size Guide
If you use our clothing size recommender, the information you supply, along with a unique identifier, will be processed by Prime AI Ltd to recommend a product size based on the criteria you supply. If you place an order, Prime AI will use your order data and returns information to help improve the accuracy of the size recommender. Your data will be handled in accordance with Prime AI’s
privacy policy
.
Placing and Processing Orders
When you place an order with us, your name, billing address, shipping address, payment information (including credit card numbers), email address, and phone number are used in order to fulfil the contract and process your order. When you place an order through our website, Shopify will retain your personal information unless and until you ask us to erase it for you.
Your name and delivery contact information is transferred tour our fulfilment provider and the courier(s) used to send your order – they will handle your data according to their privacy policy, and might transfer it outside of the EEA:
James and James Fulfilment Limited (
privacy policy
)
