Thank you for choosing PRIME AI.
This page describes how we collect, store and process your data. We are committed to protecting
                        your privacy and security online. We may update Privacy Policy from time to time, so please
                        check this page regularly if you would like to keep up to date with our latest policy. Last
                        policy update: 15th December 2023.
PRIME AI LTD, registered in UK under company number 11599467, is the operator of the
                        website
https://www.primeai.co.uk
and
https://findclothesbypicture.com/
We are responsible for the provision of software as service to apparel and footwear retailers to
                        provide personalised shopping experience to their customers in their web and physical stores.
                        These services include applications for clothing, shoes, bras sizing recommendations, advanced
                        image analysis, measuring body parts virtually, dynamic content and product recommendations,
                        back in stock alerts via emails and sms, personalised content delivery on retailer's web
                        shop, emails, notification to shoppers mobile phones and analytics platform.
Please refer to the retailer's privacy policy and preference settings on their website to
                        opt out of unwanted services. This Privacy Policy does not apply to information collected by
                        Prime AI services you may access through the retailer’s websites or submit to retailers
                        through offline or electronically.
If you have any questions regarding the use of your personal information, our policy or any other
                        data protections enquiries, please contacts us via:
our contact form
Personally Identifiable Information
We do not collect Personally Identifiable Information via our partner's websites unless it
                        is provided to us directly by shoppers in accordance with the retailer's, app store’s
                        privacy policy and data processing agreements that vary by client.
Personally Identifiable Information that may be collected, but not limited to
https://www.primeai.co.uk
and
https://findclothesbypicture.com/
websites, partner’s platforms selling, advertising, reviewing Prime AI’s software
                        and services, social media networks, emails, telephone or any other means of communication: full
                        name, email address, company name, telephone number, postal address, pictures of body parts or
                        any other pictures/files you may upload/send, username, billing information, ip address that is
                        required to supply you with Prime AI services or when you are testing Prime AI services. You are
                        generally informed about where this information will be used and we will only use it for the
                        purpose it was provided. We do not sell this information to anyone.
If you contact us via any means we may keep a record of your contact information and
                        correspondence.
Subscriber lists, Campaign content and Campaign reports
The Prime AI ensures that all subscriber lists, message content and reports remain private and
                        confidential. The Prime AI may scan/copy the content of your campaigns to ensure it complies
                        with the Terms. The Prime AI will not sell, rent, loan or invite external access to a
                        customer’s contact lists. Nor will Prime AI themselves use customer’s contact lists
                        for any purpose.
Pseudonymised Information
Pseudonyms are created when our systems read information upon your interaction with Prime
                        AI's software on retailer's websites and Prime AI website.
For example, we collect information: Device, browsers, operating system type you are using,
                        location, purchase history, viewed items history and your behaviour on the website, referrer
                        address log files and other data sets. This enables Prime AI to optimise, improve and
                        personalise website visitors' shopping experience.
When you visit Prime AI website we are using Google Analytics, Google ads, Google signals,
                        Engagebay to collect and analyse information about the use of our website. This information
                        helps us serve relevant advertisements to you on Google, and also helps us to measure the
                        effectiveness of our marketing campaigns. We also use YouTube, Facebook, Instagram, Twitter and
                        LinkedIn to collect and analyse information about the use of our website and interactions with
                        Prime AI business on social networks. This information helps us serve relevant advertisements to
                        you and measure the effectiveness of our marketing campaigns.
Both types of information usability
• Process, manage, complete and account for transactions, including purchases and refund,
                        exchange requests;
• Provide our products and services to you and fulfil your orders;
• Identify your product and service preferences;
• Improve merchandise selections and customer service;
• Invite you to participate in customer research;
• Notify you about products, services, features, promotions, events and special offerings
                        relating to the Prime AI services and assisting your shopping journey on our partner's
                        websites that we think you will find valuable;
• Provide customer support and respond to your requests, comments and inquiries;
• Administer your participation in promotions, contests and sweepstakes;
• Secure our operations and help prevent fraud, unauthorized activity;
• Operate, evaluate and improve our business (including developing products and services,
                        managing our communications, performing market research, and administering our websites and
                        mobile apps);
• Transmit anonymised data to the retailer in order to improve their products, services and
                        your shopping experience;
• We can associate anonymised user information with retailer's information from the
                        accounts that have expressly consented to this association in accordance with the
                        retailer's own privacy policy;
• All aggregated and pseudonymised data may be used to identify and provide cross device
                        size recommendations.
We also may use the information in other ways for which we provide specific notice at the time of
                        collection.
Preferences Settings
• We collect the information provided by Google from user accounts that have consented to
                        this on Google provided services. This information may include user location, google search
                        history, YouTube history and data from sites that partner with Google. Such data may be accessed
                        and/or deleted by users for such association via Google My Activity;
• You can opt-out of the from Google Analytics opt out here;
• Anonymised data may be used and collected by Google integrated services that require
                        Google Ads, remarketing with Google Analytics, Google Analytics Demographics and Interest
                        Reporting, Google Display Network Impression Reporting, to build a profile of your interests and
                        show you personalised adverts on other sites. Opt out from personalised ads: opt out;
• Opt out from Facebook marketing platform here;
• You may also opt out of the automated collection of information by certain third-party ad
                        networks for the purpose of delivering advertisements tailored to your interests, by visiting
                        the consumer here;
• You can visit the Digital Advertising Alliance self-regulatory program opt-out page here
                        find and select Prime AI to opt out.
Opt out from our Direct Marketing communications use provided link “Unsubscribe” in
                        our email or sms communications.
Children's Privacy
Our website and software services are not directed at children. If we are made aware that we have
                        received personally identifiable information for someone under 18, we will use reasonable
                        efforts to remove that information from our records as per the Children's Online Privacy
                        Protection Act.
Cookies
Cookies are files which website and widget use in order to work properly and provide important
                        visitor data to us. In order for our service to be functional. These files are automatically
                        stored by your browser on your device when visiting a website or interacting with a size
                        recommendation widgets, back in stock alerts or dynamic content recommendations. However, you
                        can configure your computer in such a way that no cookies are stored on your computer.
Pixel tags or clear GIFs
To help us understand the effectiveness of select communications and marketing efforts, we may
                        use "message format" and "message open" sensing technologies that use pixel
                        tags or clear GIFs (which are also called web beacons). These technologies allow us to know if
                        your email program is able to accept HTML emails and, if it is, to: send you emails in that
                        format, determine if you have opened our e-mail messages, and completed a purchase.
Outside sources
We may collect Personal Information about you from retail partners, business partners,
                        contractors, and other third parties. This includes, but is not limited to, instances in which
                        you affirmatively authorise those third parties to provide us with Personal Information. For
                        example, retail partners may provide us with Personal Information about items you have purchased
                        from them in the past so that we can provide better fit recommendations for you. This Personal
                        Information is shared with us in accordance with that third party’s privacy policy. If you
                        have any questions or concerns about the information that we may have received about you, please
                        contact us.
User agreement
By continuing to use our website and services, you agree to the placement of cookies on our
                        device. You can choose not to receive cookies by disabling them on your browser. Please refer to
                        the browser provider how to disable it. If you choose not to receive our cookies, you will
                        receive limited functionalities and we cannot guarantee that you will be satisfied with the
                        experience.
Retaining data
When storing data, we aim to retain the data for no longer than is necessary for the purpose in
                        which it was obtained, with the objective to ensure the highest level of data accuracy. Where
                        identified as inaccurate, data is either rectified or destroyed in a secure manner. Data
                        retention periods may vary between operational activities, with the business providing
                        consideration as to the length of time data is held for on a case by case basis.
Regarding storage, there are several ways in which your data may be stored: within cloud servers.
                        When utilising platforms to fulfil our operational requirements, third party solutions may be
                        used to store the data. As a company, we aim to utilise partners who have data centres within
                        the European Economic Area (EEA), United Kingdom and India (for users from India only).
Personal information collected from visitors outside of the European Economic Area (EEA), may be
                        transferred to European Economic Area (EEA) or United Kingdom data centres. By doing business or
                        interacting with Prime AI, you are consenting to the transfer of your Personal Information to
                        facilities located in the European Economic Area (EEA) and United Kingdom.
Your rights
In line with the General Data Protection Regulation, you have the following rights:
• To see what information we hold on you, please contact us for Subject Access Request Form
                        this will be used to confirm your identity;
• Right to be forgotten – Once you know what personal information we hold on you, you
                        can request us to delete the relevant information;
• Right to object from us processing your data – after your identity is confirmed and
                        data identified. Your personal data can be deleted and will not be processed anymore;
• Right to correct your data – If any of your personal data we hold isn't
                        accurate, let us know and we will get it updated for you.
We aim to comply with legislation and respond within thirty days of receiving personal data
                        requests.
Third parties seeking access to an individual's data should initially contact the individual
                        regarding such requests.
Supervisory authority
By continuing to use our website and services, you agree to the placement of cookies on our
                        device. You can choose not to receive cookies by disabling them on your browser. Please refer to
                        the browser provider how to disable it. If you choose not to receive our cookies, you will
                        receive limited functionalities and we cannot guarantee that you will be satisfied with the
                        experience.
We follow guidance from the ICO (Information Commissioner's Office), they are the UK's
                        independent supervisory body that uphold information rights. The ICO have stated in line with
                        the GDPR that we have to provide you information on how we process personal data:
• Concise, transparent, intelligible and easily accessible;
• Written in clear and plain language;
• Free of charge;
Notice to California Residents
