Consumer Services Privacy Policy Annex
Scope
This Consumer Services Privacy Policy Annex supplements our general Privacy Policy and applies solely to the processing of personal information that we collect in connection with the Consumer Services.
For example, you may create a Narvar profile when you opt-in to Narvar’s Consumer Services on a Merchant website and provide information for delivery preferences, opt-in to SMS or email communications about all shipments from Merchants, or save or use your return preferences.
In addition, when you create a Narvar profile, we may collect any personal information about you that has been collected by a Merchant and add this to your Narvar profile.
Consumer Services - Personal Information We Collect
In connection with the Consumer Services, Narvar may collect the following personal information about you:
Personal Information You Provide to Us.
We may collect personal information you provide about yourself like your name, address, email address, and phone number.
Personal Information Collected by Merchants.
By signing up for a Narvar Profile, you expressly authorize us to collect, and the Merchant to provide, any personal information about you collected by the Merchant that is associated with your Narvar Profile.
Personal Information We Collect Automatically
. We may collect personal information automatically in connection with your use of the Consumer Services. For example, this may include personal information about how you access and use the Consumer Services, including information about your transactions and other interactions with Merchants, the device and browser you use, your network connection, your IP address, and other details about how you use the Consumer Services. We may collect some of this personal information by using “cookies” or other similar technologies.
Personal Information We Collect from Other Third Parties.
We may collect personal information from third parties. These third parties may include, but are not limited to, other Merchants that process personal information about you, data brokers and other commercially available sources.
Consumer Services - How We Use Your Personal Information
We use personal information for a variety of business purposes, including to provide the Consumers Services, for administrative purposes, and to provide you with marketing, as described below.
Provide the Consumer Services.
We use personal information to fulfill our contract with you and provide the Consumer Services, such as:
‍
‍
Completing transactions;
Pre-filling delivery and return preferences and information;
Providing you with requested updates for shipments from Merchants;
Providing you with recommendations of other drop off locations near the addresses you provide;
Providing access to certain areas, functionalities, and features of the Consumer Services;
Answering requests for support;
Communicating with you; and
Allowing you to register for events.
Administrative Purposes
. We use personal information for various administrative purposes, such as:
‍
‍
Pursuing our legitimate interests such as direct marketing, research and development (including marketing research), network and information security, and fraud prevention;
Detecting security incidents, protecting against malicious, deceptive, fraudulent or illegal activity, and prosecuting those responsible for that activity;
Carrying out analytics;
Measuring interest and engagement in the Consumer Services;
Improving, upgrading, or enhancing the Consumer Services;
Developing new products and services;
Creating de-identified and/or aggregated information. If we create or receive de-identified information, we will not attempt to reidentify such information, unless permitted by, or required to comply with, applicable laws;
Ensuring internal quality control and safety;
Authenticating and verifying individual identities, including requests to exercise your rights under this Consumer Services Privacy Policy Annex;
Debugging to identify and repair errors with the Consumer Services;
Auditing relating to interactions, transactions, and other compliance activities;
Sharing personal information with third parties as needed to provide the Consumer Services or as otherwise permitted by applicable law;
Enforcing our agreements and policies; and
Carrying out activities that are required to comply with our legal obligations.
Marketing.
We may use personal information to tailor and provide you with marketing and other content. We may provide you with these materials as permitted by applicable law.
With Your Consent.
We may use personal information for other purposes that are clearly disclosed to you at the time you provide personal information or with your consent.
Automated Decision-Making.
We may engage in automated decision-making, including profiling.
If you have questions about our automated decision making, you may contact us as set forth in “Contact Us” above.
Other Purposes.
We also use personal information for other purposes as requested by you or as permitted by applicable law.
Consumer Services - Disclosing Your Personal Information to Third Parties
We disclose personal information to third parties for a variety of business purposes, including Merchants you share or interact with, if we sell your personal information to other third parties, service providers, to protect us or others, or in the event of a corporate transaction such as a merger, sale, or asset transfer, as described below and as described in the general Privacy Policy.
Merchants You Share or Interact With.
The Services may allow you to share personal information or interact with Merchants.
For example, when you use information saved to your Narvar profile to apply delivery or return preferences to a transaction with a Merchant, your personal information will be shared with the Merchant.
Once your personal information is shared with the Merchant, it will also be subject to the Merchant’s privacy policy. We are not responsible for the processing of your personal information by Merchants.
Third Parties We Sell or Disclose Personal Information To.
We may sell or make available personal information to third parties as permitted by applicable law.
Once your personal information is shared with a third party, it will also be subject to the third party’s privacy policy.
We are not responsible for the processing of your personal information by these third parties.
