Fraud Prevention Services Privacy Policy Annex
Scope
This Fraud Prevention Services Privacy Policy Annex supplements our general Privacy Policy and applies solely to the processing of personal information that we collect in connection with the Fraud Prevention Services.
The Fraud Prevention Services are offered by Narvar to help Merchants and other third parties detect and prevent fraud and abuse.
Fraud Prevention Services - Personal Information We Collect
In connection with the Fraud Prevention Services, Narvar may collect the following personal information about you:
Personal Information You Provide to Us.
We may collect personal information you provide about yourself to Narvar like your name, address, email address, and phone number. For example, this includes personal information that you provide to us when you sign up for a Narvar Profile in connection with your use of the Consumer Services.
Personal Information Collected by Merchants.
By signing up for a Narvar Profile, you expressly authorize us to collect, and the Merchant to provide, any personal information about you collected by the Merchant that is associated with your Narvar Profile.
Personal Information We Collect Automatically
. We may collect personal information automatically in connection with our provision of the Fraud Prevention Services. For example, this may include personal information about how you access and use the Consumer Services, including information about your transactions and other interactions with Merchants, the device and browser you use, your network connection, your IP address, and other details about how you use the Consumer Services. We may collect some of this personal information by using “cookies” or other similar technologies.
Personal Information We Collect from Other Third Parties.
We may collect personal information from third parties. These third parties may include, but are not limited to, Merchants that process personal information about you, data brokers, and other commercially available sources.
Fraud Prevention Services - How We Use Your Personal Information
We use personal information for a variety of business purposes, including to provide the Fraud Prevention Services and for administrative purposes, as described below.
Provide the Fraud Prevention Services.
We use personal information to fulfill our contracts and provide the Fraud Prevention Services to Merchants and other third parties.
‍
Administrative Purposes
. We use personal information for various administrative purposes, such as:
‍
‍
Pursuing our legitimate interests such as research and development, network and information security, and fraud prevention;
Detecting security incidents, protecting against malicious, deceptive, fraudulent or illegal activity, and prosecuting those responsible for that activity;
Carrying out analytics;
Improving, upgrading, or enhancing the Fraud Prevention Services;
Developing new products and services;
Creating de-identified and/or aggregated information. If we create or receive de-identified information, we will not attempt to reidentify such information, unless permitted by, or required to comply with, applicable laws;
Ensuring internal quality control and safety;
Authenticating and verifying individual identities, including requests to exercise your rights under this Fraud Prevention Services Privacy Policy Annex;
Debugging to identify and repair errors with the Fraud Prevention Services;
Auditing relating to interactions, transactions, and other compliance activities;
Sharing personal information with third parties as needed to provide the Fraud Prevention Services or as otherwise permitted by applicable law;
Enforcing our agreements and policies; and
Carrying out activities that are required to comply with our legal obligations.
With Your Consent.
We may use personal information for other purposes that are clearly disclosed to you at the time you provide personal information or with your consent.
Automated Decision-Making.
We may engage in automated decision-making, including profiling. Narvar analyzes personal information to detect and prevent fraud and abuse. Narvar provides related information to its customers. Narvar’s customers may use the information provided to them by Narvar in connection with their fraud and abuse prevention programs and as otherwise permitted by applicable law. Narvar may also use personal information as otherwise set forth above.
If you have questions about our automated decision-making, you may contact us as set forth in “Contact Us” above.
Colorado Privacy Act Disclosures.
To the extent our automated decision-making is (1) profiling in furtherance of decisions that produce legal or similarly significant effects concerning a consumer and (2) subject to the Colorado Privacy Act, then the information immediately below also applies to this processing:
‍
‍
What decisions are subject to profiling?
Narvar analyzes personal information to detect and prevent fraud and abuse. Narvar provides related information to its customers. Narvar’s customers may use the information provided to them by Narvar in connection with their fraud and abuse prevention programs and as otherwise permitted by applicable law. Narvar may also use personal information as otherwise set forth above.
What are the categories of personal information to be processed as part of the profiling in furtherance of decisions that produce legal or other similarly significant effects?
Narvar may use any personal information that it processes about you in connection with the profiling in furtherance of decisions that produce legal or other similarly significant effects. This may include, but is not limited to, information about the device you are using to interact with a Narvar customer, order details, and shipping address.
Explanation of the logic used in the profiling process:
The logic used by Narvar is aimed at detecting and preventing fraud and abuse. For example, Narvar may assess whether or not a shipping address has previously been associated with fraudulent orders.
Explanation of how profiling is used in the decision-making process:
Narvar analyzes personal information to detect and prevent fraud and abuse. Narvar provides related information to its customers. Narvar’s customers may use the information provided to them by Narvar in connection with their fraud and abuse prevention programs and as otherwise permitted by applicable law. Narvar may also use personal information as otherwise set forth above.
The benefits and potential consequences of the decision based on the profiling:
The benefits and potential consequences of the decision based on the profiling are controlled by the Narvar customer that uses the information provided by Narvar. Narvar’s primary goal is to help companies detect and prevent fraud and abuse.
How can I opt out of Narvar’s profiling in furtherance of decisions that produce legal or other similarly significant effects?
Please follow the instructions in the section titled “Your Privacy Rights” in the general Privacy Policy.
Other Purposes.
We also use personal information for other purposes as requested by you or as permitted by applicable law.
‍
Fraud Prevention Services - Disclosing Your Personal Information to Third Parties
We disclose personal information to third parties for a variety of business purposes, including Merchants or other third parties you interact with, if we sell your personal information to other third parties, service providers, to protect us or others, or in the event of a corporate transaction such as a merger, sale, or asset transfer, as described below and as described in the general Privacy Policy.
Merchants or Other Third Parties You Interact With.
If you attempt to interact or transact with a Merchant or other third party that uses the Fraud Prevention Services, we may provide them with your personal information as part of the standard functionality of the Fraud Prevention Services.
Once your personal information is shared with the Merchant or other third party, it will also be subject to such party’s privacy policy. We are not responsible for the processing of your personal information by Merchants or other third parties.
Third Parties We Sell or Disclose Personal Information To.
We may sell or make available personal information to third parties as permitted by applicable law.
Once your personal information is shared with a third party, it will also be subject to the third party’s privacy policy.
We are not responsible for the processing of your personal information by these third parties.
