Additional Privacy Rights for California Residents
Disclosure Regarding “Sales” of Personal Information under the CCPA.
In the preceding twelve months from the effective date, Narvar has not “sold” any personal information (as defined by the CCPA), nor does Narvar have actual knowledge of any “sale” of personal information of minors under 16 years of age.
Disclosure Regarding Cross-Context Behavioral Advertising under the CCPA.
In the preceding twelve months from the effective date, Narvar has not “shared” any personal information for “cross-context behavioral advertising” (as such terms are defined in the CCPA), nor does Narvar have actual knowledge of any “sharing” of personal information of minors under 16 years of age for “cross-context behavioral advertising”.
Opting Out of “Sales” of Personal Information and/or “Sharing” for “Cross-Context Behavioral Advertising” under the CCPA.
California residents have the right to opt out of the “sale” of personal information and the “sharing” of personal information for “cross-context behavioral advertising.” California residents may exercise these rights clicking on the following link and following the instructions on that page:
Privacy Settings
Disclosure Regarding Sensitive Personal Information under the CCPA.
Narvar may use and disclose sensitive personal information in accordance with the Fraud Prevention Services Privacy Policy Annex and the applicable sections of the general Privacy Policy.
Right to Limit Use and Disclosure of Sensitive Personal Information under the CCPA.
California residents have the right to limit certain uses and disclosures of “sensitive personal information” by Narvar in connection with the Fraud Prevention Services. California residents may exercise these rights clicking on the following link and following the instructions on that page:
Privacy Settings
.
Non-Discrimination.
California residents have the right not to receive discriminatory treatment by us for the exercise of their rights conferred by the CCPA.
